### Generate Text with Aihubmix Gemini Model (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/vercel/ai/blob/main/content/providers/03-community-providers/04-aihubmix.mdx

Generate text using the `generateText` function and an Aihubmix Gemini model. This example shows how to target Google's Gemini models through the Aihubmix provider.

```typescript
import { aihubmix } from '@aihubmix/ai-sdk-provider';
import { generateText } from 'ai';

const { text } = await generateText({
  model: aihubmix('gemini-2.5-flash'),
  prompt: 'Create a Python script to sort a list of numbers.',
});
```

--------------------------------

### Generate Text with Google Vertex in Node.js

Source: https://github.com/vercel/ai/blob/main/packages/google-vertex/README.md

Use the default vertex provider instance to generate text with gemini-2.5-flash model in Node.js runtime. Requires GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS environment variable set to a JSON credentials file path.

```typescript
import { vertex } from '@ai-sdk/google-vertex';
import { generateText } from 'ai';

const { text } = await generateText({
  model: vertex('gemini-2.5-flash'),
  prompt: 'Write a vegetarian lasagna recipe.',
});
```

--------------------------------

### Gemini Web Search with Google Search Tool

Source: https://github.com/vercel/ai/blob/main/content/cookbook/05-node/56-web-search-agent.mdx

Enable search grounding with compatible Gemini models to access the latest information using Google search. Access grounding metadata and safety ratings from provider metadata.

```typescript
import { google } from '@ai-sdk/google';
import { generateText } from 'ai';

const { text, sources, providerMetadata } = await generateText({
  model: 'google/gemini-2.5-flash',
  tools: {
    google_search: google.tools.googleSearch({}),
  },
  prompt:
    'List the top 5 San Francisco news from the past week.' +
    'You must include the date of each article.',
});

console.log(text);
console.log(sources);

// access the grounding metadata.
const metadata = providerMetadata?.google;
const groundingMetadata = metadata?.groundingMetadata;
const safetyRatings = metadata?.safetyRatings;
```

--------------------------------

### Use Google URL Context with AI SDK

Source: https://github.com/vercel/ai/blob/main/content/providers/01-ai-sdk-providers/15-google.mdx

Shows how to enable the `url_context` tool to allow Gemini 2.0 Flash models and above to analyze specific URLs provided in the prompt.

```typescript
import { google } from '@ai-sdk/google';
import { generateText } from 'ai';

const { text, sources, providerMetadata } = await generateText({
  model: google('gemini-2.5-flash'),
  prompt: `Based on the document: https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/url-context.
          Answer this question: How many links we can consume in one request?`,
  tools: {
    url_context: google.tools.urlContext({})
  }
});

const metadata = providerMetadata?.google as
  | GoogleProviderMetadata
  | undefined;
const groundingMetadata = metadata?.groundingMetadata;
const urlContextMetadata = metadata?.urlContextMetadata;
```

--------------------------------

### Generate Images with Google Gemini 2.5 Flash using AI SDK (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/vercel/ai/blob/main/content/cookbook/00-guides/20-google-gemini-image-generation.mdx

This snippet demonstrates how to generate new images using the `generateText` function from the AI SDK with the `google/gemini-2.5-flash-image` model. It shows how to provide a text prompt, retrieve the generated images from the `result.files` array as `Uint8Array` data, and save them to the local filesystem. Dependencies include `ai`, `node:fs`, and `dotenv` for environment variables.

